<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,152,758]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,538,564]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[330,654,538,563]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="streptocephala">
<emphasis box="[330,654,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Haplosyllis streptocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first described within the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1108,1174,538,563]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1108,1174,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Syllis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but its chaetal shape agrees with 
<taxonomicName box="[297,433,577,602]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[297,433,577,602]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Haplosyllis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Their chaetae are highly characteristic, broad and totally unidentate from medium body to posterior end. Both palps and prostomium are much thinner than the rest of the body, which distinguishes it from other 
<taxonomicName box="[483,622,655,680]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[483,622,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Haplosyllis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. As the description is based only on the 
<typeStatus box="[1220,1330,654,680]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">holotype</typeStatus>
, it is not possible to assess whether this is a species-specific characteristic (or a peculiarity of that particular specimen), as well as to provide ecological and reproduction data.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
